Doc Del,<br><br>
The men that were CO medics were not &quot;better than you&quot;. It would bother them to have you feel that way! That is what was so great about them. They were secure in who they were and what they were doing. They had no need to be condescending. They had their job to do and we ours. But they were there. I also knew medics who carried weapons and they were cut out of the same cloth as those that didn't. In my opinion medics in the field and those who served on dustoffs w/crews were the bravest of the brave. God bless all!<br><br>
All who served in RVN Welcome home!
